The power utility is planning to challenge the national regulator in court over a tariff increase, it says is not enough. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG – Eskom is planning to challenge the national regulator in court over a tariff increase, it says is not enough. The power utility was granted a price increase of 9.4-percent in April, which is 17-percent less than what it had requested. READ: Moody's: Eskom's bailout credit negative Government has committed to financially assist the debt-ridden utility. The bailout for Eskom this financial year is R49-billion, increasing to R56-billion the next year.